=== Network management with netifrc scripts ===

When [[netifrc]] scripts are being used as the primary method to control network interfaces {{c|dhcpcd}} can be used as the DHCP client. All that is necessary for operation is that each interface be set to <code>dhcp</code> in {{Path|/etc/conf.d/net}}. See the [[Handbook:AMD64/Networking/Introduction|Network configuration]] section of the Gentoo Handbook for more information.

In this configuration {{c|dhcpcd}} will conflict with netifrc scripts if added to a run level. Verify it has been removed:

{{RootCmd|rc-update del dhcpcd default}}

=== Static IP addresses ===

In case the network interface card should be configured with a static IP address, add their data to {{Path|/etc/dhcpcd.conf}}.<ref name=manpage /> The following is an example of manually adding a static address, routes, and DNS by editing DHCPCD's configuration file using a text editor of choice:

{{FileBox|filename=/etc/dhcpcd.conf|lang=bash|1=
static ip_address=192.168.0.10/24
static routers=192.168.0.1
static domain_name_servers=192.168.0.1
}}

